                                    <version>Lustre 2.1.5</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="53718" author="jlevi" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 14:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1468&quot; title=&quot;Support Compat RDMA for O2IB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1468&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1468&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53674" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 03:07:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have confirmed that it need ofed 3.5. This means this issue is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1468&quot; title=&quot;Support Compat RDMA for O2IB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1468&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1468&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53673" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 02:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ofed define this in rcupdate.h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#include_next &amp;lt;linux/rcupdate.h&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#define RCU_INIT_POINTER(p, v) p = v&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;starting kernel 2.6.32-279.22.1 rcupdate also define&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;/**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RCU_INIT_POINTER() - initialize an RCU protected pointer&lt;br/&gt;
 *&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Initialize an RCU-protected pointer in such a way to avoid RCU-lockdep&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;splats.&lt;br/&gt;
 */&lt;br/&gt;
#define RCU_INIT_POINTER(p, v) \&lt;br/&gt;
                p = (typeof(*v) __force __rcu *)(v)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;p&gt;This caused conflict redefine during the build&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53671" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 01:06:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think so. It&apos;s interesting that lustre-master is building 2.6.32.279.19.1.el6 on ofed 1.5.4 and passes. I&apos;ll investigate this more by building this manually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53669" author="pjones" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 00:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So essentially this issue is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1468&quot; title=&quot;Support Compat RDMA for O2IB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1468&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1468&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53668" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 00:44:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should move the build system to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/release_notes/OFED_3.5_release_notes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/release_notes/OFED_3.5_release_notes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53667" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 00:42:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The kernel that the patch landed was RHEL6.3 2.6.32-279.22.1.el6&lt;br/&gt;
ofed-1.5.4 does not support this kernel&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; o   Linux Operating Systems:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RedHat EL5 up6	2.6.18-238.el5&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RedHat EL5 up7	2.6.18-274.el5&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RedHat EL6		2.6.32-71.el6&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RedHat EL6.1		2.6.32-131.0.15.el6&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RedHat EL6.2 		2.6.32-220.el6&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="53666" author="mdiep" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 00:37:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, sure&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53649" author="pjones" created="Sat, 9 Mar 2013 12:27:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this as your top priority?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
